{
    "name": "Burning Child",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Born from the traumatic death of an abducted human child at the hands of orc alchemists seeking to unlock the mysteries of his sorcerous bloodline and convert him into a weapon, the Burning Child has haunted a wide stretch of wasteland in eastern Belkzen for centuries.<br/><br/>First seen during the battle that bears his name, the Burning Child continues to wander in an endless search for his parents, constantly reliving the terrifying experience of his first fiery death. While in his passive state, he\u2019s little more than disembodied sobbing and the scent of burning flesh. But when he happens upon the scene of a battle, the memory of his agonizing death pushes him to manifest, and he wanders into the fray crying out for rescue, all the while unintentionally sowing devastation as the uncontrollable energies coursing through him spill out of his unstable form."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>The smell of scorched flesh accompanies this small child, who appears to be made entirely of dust and smoldering ash.</i>",
